# Chief — environment variables.
# Copy to .env.local and fill in. NEVER commit real values; .env* is gitignored.

# --- Supabase (Phase 1) ---
# Project settings → API. The anon key is safe for the browser; RLS enforces access.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# --- Anthropic (default AI provider — Chief runs on it; also powers KB
#     classify-on-save and merge). Get a key at console.anthropic.com.
#     REQUIRED unless you switch to AI Gateway (see below). ---
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# Optional override; defaults to the chief.model setting (claude-opus-4-8).
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8

# --- AI Gateway (optional alternative to a direct Anthropic key) ---
# Route Chief's model calls through Vercel AI Gateway instead of straight to
# Anthropic: one endpoint, any model, and no console.anthropic.com key to
# fetch. Turn it on in-app (Config → AI — provider = "gateway"), not here.
# On a Vercel deployment NOTHING is needed below — the project's OIDC token
# authenticates automatically and usage bills to your own Vercel account.
# Set AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY only for LOCAL dev (no OIDC token locally):
#   run `vercel env pull .env.local` to fetch one, or paste a gateway key.
# AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=
# AI_PROVIDER=gateway   # env fallback if you'd rather not use the in-app setting

# --- Voyage embeddings (optional — semantic KB search; without it the KB
#     degrades gracefully to full-text search) ---
# VOYAGE_API_KEY=

# --- Google / Gmail (Phase 4 — the inbox) ---
# Your OWN Google Cloud OAuth client (sovereign: your project, your consent
# screen, your tokens — stored only in your own database). Setup:
#   1. Create a Google Cloud project; enable the "Gmail API" and the
#      "Gmail MCP API" (gmailmcp.googleapis.com).
#   2. Google Auth Platform → configure the consent screen; under Data Access
#      add scopes: gmail.modify, gmail.compose, gmail.send.
#   3. Create an OAuth client (Web application) with redirect URI
#      https://YOUR-DOMAIN/api/google/callback (and http://localhost:3000/api/google/callback for dev).
#   4. Put the client ID/secret here, deploy, then tap Connect Gmail on the
#      Inbox screen.
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
